Heritage Bank has said that its target in the next few years is to groom, nurture, grow and bring at least three Small and Medium scale Enterprises (SMEs) to list on the Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE). Managing Director of Heritage Bank Limited, Ifie Sekibo, who said this at a media parley in Lagos on Tuesday stressed that the financial institution’s strategic focus of helping to nurture SMEs which would form the back bone of the Nigerian economic development and growth. “In the next three to five years we should have successfully taken and listed three companies on the Nigerian Stock Exchange”, he said. He explained that Heritage Bank was a service bank, which adopts creativity and innovation to carry out its banking services.